{
    "abstract": "Evolution is a fundamental process that shapes the biological world we inhabit, and reinforcement learning is a powerful tool used in artificial intelligence to develop intelligent agents that learn from their environment. In recent years, researchers have explored the connections between these two seemingly distinct fields, and have found compelling evidence that they are more closely related than previously thought. This paper examines these connections and their implications, highlighting the potential for reinforcement learning principles to enhance our understanding of evolution and the role of feedback in evolutionary systems.",
